ous voices that mark a self at any time. An event, as he elaborates it, is what disturbs or inspires thinking as it activates layered sheets of memory. A memory sheet itself assembles recollections, dispositions organized from the past, and vague remains that carry efficacies.Resounding Events shows how resonances between event and memory can help forge new concepts better adjusted to an emergent situation. Addressing tensions between working class experience and norms of the academy, his father’s coma, antiwar protests, the growing disaffection of the white working class, the neoliberalization of the university, climate denialism, and his sister’s experience with workers shifting to Trump, Connolly shows how engaged intellectuals become worthy of the events they encounter.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2022) 0aMemoryzUnited States. 0aRecollection (Psychology). 0aThought and thinking. 0aWorking class white peoplezUnited States. 0aWorking classzUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aEvent.  aFoucault.  aGilles Deleuze.  aProust.  aWriting.  acreative thought.  ademocracy.  afascism.  aideology.  amemory.  amimesis.  atemporality.  athe working class.  auniversity life.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075166640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781531500252zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781531500252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781531500252/original  a978-3-11-075166-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK